rcinogenic effects?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Aldehydes","Benzene derivatives","Nitrosamines","Phenolic compounds","Polycyclic aromatic hydrocarbons"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENitrosamines\u003C/strong\u003E are potent carcinogenic compounds found in both alcohol and tobacco products. They cause DNA damage through alkylation of nucleic acids, leading to mutations that can result in cancer development.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPolycyclic aromatic hydrocarbons\u003C/strong\u003E are primarily found in tobacco smoke but not alcohol. \u003Cstrong\u003EBenzene derivatives\u003C/strong\u003E are mainly present in tobacco smoke. \u003Cstrong\u003EAldehydes\u003C/strong\u003E like acetaldehyde are found in alcohol but are not the primary carcinogenic compound. \u003Cstrong\u003EPhenolic compounds\u003C/strong\u003E are present in tobacco but are not the main carcinogenic agents.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Nitrosamines found in alcohol and tobacco are carcinogenic compounds that increase risk of squamous cell carcinoma.","Nitrosamines cause DNA damage through alkylation of nucleic acids."],"references":["Hadian Y, Howell JY, Ramsey ML, et al. Cutaneous Squamous Cell Carcinoma. [Updated 2024 Jul 2]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK441939/","Li K, Ricker K, Tsai FC, Hsieh CJ, Osborne G, Sun M, Marder ME, Elmore S, Schmitz R, Sandy MS. Estimated Cancer Risks Associated with Nitrosamine Contamination in Commonly Used Medications. Int J Environ Res Public Health. 2021 Sep 8;18(18):9465. doi: 10.3390/ijerph18189465. PMID: 34574388; PMCID: PMC8467924.","Burton KA, Ashack KA, Khachemoune A. Cutaneous Squamous Cell Carcinoma: A Review of High-Risk and Metastatic Disease. Am J Clin Dermatol. 2016 Oct;17(5):491-508. doi: 10.1007/s40257-016-0207-3. PMID: 27358187.","Que SKT, Zwald FO, Schmults CD. Cutaneous squamous cell carcinoma: Incidence, risk factors, diagnosis, and staging. J Am Acad Dermatol. 2018 Feb;78(2):237-247. doi: 10.1016/j.jaad.2017.08.059. PMID: 29332704."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52771"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15205"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52771","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/52771"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-04T20:20:32+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-04T20:21:08+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7896"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"67319"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"4928","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4928"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udca9","name":"Gastrointestinal","synonyms"